reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It's a fabulous valuable phone at a cheap price. It has a durable phone case so I don't need to worry about dropping it off. I love the map function the best for the detail of GPS compared with my old phone. And I like the fast smart toch screenshot button on the screen for any information I read. Meanwhile, for the battery part, so far I probably charge it every four days if I don't watch any videos. This is the most economical cell phone that I ever used.

Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good resilient phone, just some irritating features
reviews.reviewText: This phone is awesome for the price if you work with your hands for a living. It tolerates drops, shocks, salt/fresh water weathering. The only things I find irritating is that the fingerprint sensor is right below the on/off button and the volume buttons right above that. If you're right handed, this sensor gets tripped all of the time, to the point where it gets disabled quite a few bit. Also, the comma is super close the the emoji button. Instead of commas when I'm typing, I'll open up the emoji screen. Oh, and it's hard to change screens from maps to anything else. Good phone, just little irritants.
